// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
//
// test/Driver/m4_emit_help.test — FR-024 driver-help surface lock.
//
// **Specification anchors**:
//   - `specs/007-m4-mlir-dialect/spec.md` FR-024, SC-009 — the
//     public `nslc` CLI surface MUST NOT mention `mlir`, `hw`, or
//     `verilog` at M4. The dialect is loaded into `mlir::MLIRContext`
//     but unreachable from the public emit-stage menu.
//   - `specs/007-m4-mlir-dialect/tasks.md` T122 (Phase 5 US3).
//
// The M3-era `nslc` driver (see `tools/nslc/main.cpp`) does not
// implement a dedicated `--help` flag; an unknown argument emits
// `unknown argument: <a>` then the canonical usage line on stderr
// and exits 2. That usage line IS the help surface this fixture
// locks. Run-time `-emit=` accepts `tokens` and `ast`; M4 MUST NOT
// silently accept `mlir` (covered separately by
// `m4_emit_mlir_rejected.test`, FR-023).

// RUN: not %nslc --help 2>&1 | FileCheck %s

// CHECK:     usage: nslc {{.*}}-emit=<stage>{{.*}}<input>
// CHECK-NOT: mlir
// CHECK-NOT: hw
// CHECK-NOT: verilog
